670
00:38:28.390 --> 00:38:32.110
Hi, thank you so much for the opportunity to present my work today on a molecular

671
00:38:32.190 --> 00:38:35.970
glue that harnesses lysine acetyltransferases to induce cell

672
00:38:36.030 --> 00:38:37.010
death in lymphoma.

673
00:38:37.830 --> 00:38:40.360
And I have no financial relationships to disclose.

674
00:38:41.420 --> 00:38:45.260
The focus of my talk today is on using small molecules to target and

675
00:38:45.290 --> 00:38:49.130
rewire cancer drivers. And small molecules fall into two

676
00:38:49.170 --> 00:38:53.110
mechanistic categories. The first is occupancy driven

677
00:38:53.130 --> 00:38:56.970
pharmacology, in which small molecules bind to a pocket on a protein,

678
00:38:57.370 --> 00:38:59.129
thereby inhibiting function.

679
00:39:00.010 --> 00:39:03.730
The second category is event-driven pharmacology, in which small

680
00:39:03.790 --> 00:39:07.470
molecules induce protein-protein interactions, the most common

681
00:39:07.530 --> 00:39:11.130
example of this being the recruitment of E3 ubiquitin ligases

682
00:39:11.490 --> 00:39:13.910
to mark a protein of interest for degradation.

683
00:39:14.970 --> 00:39:18.870
I'm going to specifically be talking about the cancer driver BCL6,

684
00:39:19.590 --> 00:39:23.260
which is deregulated in diffuse large B-cell lymphoma and becomes

685
00:39:23.330 --> 00:39:23.970
oncogenic.

686
00:39:24.770 --> 00:39:28.350
And its interactions with co-repressors mediates the

687
00:39:28.390 --> 00:39:32.090
repression of cell death pathways like P53 and Noxa

688
00:39:32.550 --> 00:39:34.730
that would normally tell the cancer cell to die.

689
00:39:35.610 --> 00:39:39.330
BCL6 is overexpressed in 40% to 60% of diffuse

690
00:39:39.390 --> 00:39:43.230
large B-cell lymphomas, which comprise around 35% of all

691
00:39:43.250 --> 00:39:46.670
non-Hodgkin's lymphomas, and this makes it a very desirable

692
00:39:46.790 --> 00:39:50.650
therapeutic. And as such, many groups have worked on developing

693
00:39:50.670 --> 00:39:54.090
loss-of-function small modalities targeting BCL6,

694
00:39:55.010 --> 00:39:58.790
including inhibitors that bind to the BTB domain, disrupting the

695
00:39:58.810 --> 00:40:02.330
interactions with co-repressors, as well as BCL6

696
00:40:02.350 --> 00:40:06.010
degraders that eliminate the protein entirely.

697
00:40:06.070 --> 00:40:09.870
However, these strategies have shown variable efficacy in

698
00:40:09.890 --> 00:40:13.530
preclinical models. And so today, I'm alternatively going to be

699
00:40:13.590 --> 00:40:16.790
talking about a gain-of-function strategy that harnesses

700
00:40:16.830 --> 00:40:18.930
BCL6 to kill lymphomas.

701
00:40:20.270 --> 00:40:24.010
And specifically, I'm going to be talking about a small molecule modality called a

702
00:40:24.070 --> 00:40:26.950
transcriptional epigenetic chemical inducer of

703
00:40:26.970 --> 00:40:30.630
proximity, which is a type of small molecule developed by the Gray and

704
00:40:30.650 --> 00:40:34.440
Krapchy Labs at Stanford University that recruits a transcriptional

705
00:40:34.510 --> 00:40:38.420
activator to cell death repressors such as BCL6, turning

706
00:40:38.470 --> 00:40:42.150
on the downstream transcription of cell death pathways and turning a

707
00:40:42.190 --> 00:40:45.910
transcriptional repression event into one of transcriptional activation.

708
00:40:47.090 --> 00:40:50.390
Our labs have demonstrated that TCIPS recruiting BRD4 and

709
00:40:50.470 --> 00:40:54.410
CDK9 can lead to very potent and selective cell killing.

710
00:40:55.590 --> 00:40:58.770
In this work, we wanted to move beyond rewiring elongation

711
00:40:58.850 --> 00:41:02.499
factors to rewiring chromatin modifiers for therapeutic

712
00:41:02.550 --> 00:41:06.490
effects in lymphoma, and therefore, we focused on the paralog

713
00:41:06.530 --> 00:41:10.150
lysine acetyltransferases P300 and CBP, which are

714
00:41:10.310 --> 00:41:13.350
associated with active transcription and enhancers.

715
00:41:13.850 --> 00:41:17.650
And they have a bromodomain that recognizes acetylated lysines, as well as a

716
00:41:17.690 --> 00:41:21.670
lysine acetyltransferase domain that catalyzes acetylation of

717
00:41:21.730 --> 00:41:24.749
histones and transcription factors.

718
00:41:24.810 --> 00:41:28.690
We hypothesized that we could develop lysine acetyltransferase-based TCIPS,

719
00:41:29.370 --> 00:41:33.250
or KatTCIPS, that recruit P300 and CBP to BCL6

720
00:41:33.270 --> 00:41:36.190
loci to drive potent cell killing of lymphoma.

721
00:41:37.210 --> 00:41:40.990
I first went about designing and developing these bivalent molecules,

722
00:41:41.470 --> 00:41:45.210
selecting the BCL6 BTB domain inhibitor BI-3812,

723
00:41:45.650 --> 00:41:48.950
and the P300 CBP selective bromodomain inhibitor

724
00:41:48.990 --> 00:41:52.930
GNE-781, and used standard medicinal chemistry

725
00:41:52.970 --> 00:41:54.720
to link the two binders together.

726
00:41:55.650 --> 00:41:59.590
Ultimately, I'll be focusing today on our lead compound, TCIP3, which contains

727
00:41:59.610 --> 00:42:01.430
a rigid piperazine linker.

728
00:42:02.330 --> 00:42:06.230
I also synthesized negative controls that ablate binding to either of

729
00:42:06.270 --> 00:42:10.250
the two proteins, but that maintain the same physicochemical properties as

730
00:42:10.290 --> 00:42:10.850
TCIP3.

731
00:42:12.030 --> 00:42:15.290
We were ultimately able to solve an X-ray co-crystal structure of a

732
00:42:15.330 --> 00:42:19.090
KatTCIP in complex with BCL6 and P300.

733
00:42:19.510 --> 00:42:22.970
You can see a BCL6 homodimer in the center, which each monomer

734
00:42:23.350 --> 00:42:26.950
binding to one KatTCIP molecule and one P300

735
00:42:26.970 --> 00:42:30.250
bromodomain. One thing that surprised us was the limited

736
00:42:30.260 --> 00:42:33.950
plasticity of ligand binding, as well as the quite small

737
00:42:33.990 --> 00:42:37.950
protein-protein interface. In fact, we only observed two neo

738
00:42:37.970 --> 00:42:41.770
hydrogen bonds forming. And so we asked the question, is this

739
00:42:41.830 --> 00:42:45.810
protein-protein interface sufficient to drive cooperative ternary

740
00:42:45.870 --> 00:42:49.770
complex assembly? And so we used isothermal calorimetry to measure

741
00:42:49.790 --> 00:42:53.110
binary and ternary KDs, which ultimately show that

742
00:42:53.150 --> 00:42:56.830
TCIP3 is able to facilitate the cooperative assembly of

743
00:42:56.850 --> 00:43:00.730
ternary complexes and is therefore a molecular glue, which may confer

744
00:43:00.830 --> 00:43:02.930
beneficial properties in cells.

745
00:43:03.890 --> 00:43:07.270
We've moved on to assessing the ability of TCIP3 to activate

746
00:43:07.290 --> 00:43:10.670
BCL6-dependent transcription in a high BCL6

747
00:43:11.350 --> 00:43:14.710
cell line, Karpas 422, using a GFP reporter assay.

748
00:43:15.230 --> 00:43:17.050
And we were able to see potent

749
00:43:18.330 --> 00:43:21.910
expression of GFP, as well as a hook effect, which is when high

750
00:43:22.010 --> 00:43:25.710
concentrations of a bivalent molecule saturate individual binding

751
00:43:25.790 --> 00:43:29.754
proteins and lead to reduced observable activity.We

752
00:43:29.774 --> 00:43:33.494
then assessed the anti-proliferative abilities of these compounds in

753
00:43:33.534 --> 00:43:37.374
the high BCL6 line, SU DHQ five. And you can

754
00:43:37.434 --> 00:43:41.204
see that compared to the parental inhibitors, negative controls, and

755
00:43:41.234 --> 00:43:45.114
various p300 Cbp modulators, tSIP3 was the

756
00:43:45.214 --> 00:43:47.954
most potent, demonstrating an IC50 of

757
00:43:48.194 --> 00:43:51.934
0.8 nanomolars in cells. And it also

758
00:43:51.974 --> 00:43:55.214
outperformed the BCL6 degrader from Arvinas,

759
00:43:55.574 --> 00:43:59.434
highlighting some of the potential benefits of gain-of-function strategies over

760
00:43:59.534 --> 00:44:00.544
loss-of-function ones.

761
00:44:01.574 --> 00:44:05.454
We also found that tSIP3 induced apoptosis over the course of

762
00:44:05.654 --> 00:44:09.423
72 hours, and we confirmed that this potency was

763
00:44:09.474 --> 00:44:13.334
dependent on the formation of a ternary complex as we dosed

764
00:44:13.394 --> 00:44:17.243
one nanomolar of tSIP3 and then were able to rescue viability

765
00:44:17.254 --> 00:44:20.774
by titrating and increasing concentrations of the BCL6

766
00:44:21.194 --> 00:44:24.394
BTP domain inhibitors, as well as GNE-781.

767
00:44:25.594 --> 00:44:29.294
We assessed the anti-proliferative effects of these compounds

768
00:44:29.334 --> 00:44:32.794
across a panel of lymphoma and leukemia cell lines with varying

769
00:44:32.834 --> 00:44:36.644
BCL6 expression, and we saw that six lymphoma lines with the

770
00:44:36.714 --> 00:44:40.694
highest BCL6 expression were the most sensitive, indicating a

771
00:44:40.714 --> 00:44:42.813
BCL6-dependent pharmacology.

772
00:44:43.794 --> 00:44:47.414
p300 and Cbp are frequently mutated across hematological

773
00:44:47.494 --> 00:44:51.354
malignancies, and so we therefore asked whether

774
00:44:51.754 --> 00:44:55.494
tSIP3 potency depended on functional p300 and Cbp

775
00:44:55.614 --> 00:44:56.014
alleles.

776
00:44:56.954 --> 00:45:00.374
And we were surprised to find that two of the cells with high BCL6

777
00:45:00.434 --> 00:45:01.154
expression that

778
00:45:02.234 --> 00:45:05.894
were sensitive to tSIP3 only contained one or three

779
00:45:05.994 --> 00:45:09.733
functional alleles, which suggested a fractional occupancy.

780
00:45:10.534 --> 00:45:14.174
And this highlights a key distinction between loss-of-function modalities,

781
00:45:14.314 --> 00:45:18.214
which must act at a full target occupancy in order to have

782
00:45:18.274 --> 00:45:22.094
therapeutic effects, and gain-of-function ones, which only require

783
00:45:22.134 --> 00:45:24.634
fractional occupancy to be potent.

784
00:45:25.174 --> 00:45:28.814
And this can allow lower doses of drug concentration and the

785
00:45:28.854 --> 00:45:30.624
avoidance of on-target toxicity.

786
00:45:31.754 --> 00:45:35.254
Moving on, we assessed what the molecular consequences of ternary

787
00:45:35.294 --> 00:45:38.814
complexes in cells would be. We performed p300 ChIP

788
00:45:38.874 --> 00:45:42.354
sequencing, where we saw an enrichment of p300 at

789
00:45:42.394 --> 00:45:45.734
BCL6 loci. We then asked if this

790
00:45:45.794 --> 00:45:48.194
localization may result in localized

791
00:45:48.854 --> 00:45:51.814
acetylation and performed ChIP sequencing of

792
00:45:51.934 --> 00:45:55.394
H3K27 acetylation, a mark of active transcription,

793
00:45:55.954 --> 00:45:59.914
and H2BK20 acetylation, which is a Cbp p300

794
00:45:59.984 --> 00:46:00.834
specific marker.

795
00:46:01.654 --> 00:46:05.614
And what we saw is that at sites that increase in acetylation, there

796
00:46:05.634 --> 00:46:09.344
was an enrichment for published BCL6 binding sites in

797
00:46:09.394 --> 00:46:12.314
human B cells and blood cancer cell lines.

798
00:46:12.374 --> 00:46:16.254
We also saw a significant acetylation of the BCL6 protein

799
00:46:16.294 --> 00:46:19.814
itself, which is consistent with reports that

800
00:46:19.884 --> 00:46:23.814
p300 is capable of acetylating the RD two domain of

801
00:46:23.854 --> 00:46:27.774
BCL6, which may contribute to de-repression of cell death pathways.

802
00:46:29.074 --> 00:46:33.014
Importantly, we did not see global losses of acetylation, suggesting

803
00:46:33.054 --> 00:46:36.474
tSIP3 is not a global HAT inhibitor or degrader.

804
00:46:37.194 --> 00:46:40.854
Finally, we performed global RNA sequencing and proteomics,

805
00:46:41.154 --> 00:46:44.594
which showed a gain of BCL6 target genes involved in cell cycle

806
00:46:44.654 --> 00:46:48.434
arrest and killing, such as p27 and ARID3B,

807
00:46:48.974 --> 00:46:52.354
and a loss of genes associated with DLBCL-specific super

808
00:46:52.394 --> 00:46:56.314
enhancers, which was a bit surprising considering that we didn't see losses

809
00:46:56.334 --> 00:47:00.034
of p300 occupancy at these regions and may reflect a

810
00:47:00.054 --> 00:47:03.274
sensitivity of enhancers to small changes in coactivator

811
00:47:03.354 --> 00:47:04.134
concentrations.

812
00:47:05.114 --> 00:47:08.814
Overall, these data point to a model in which tSIP3

813
00:47:08.874 --> 00:47:12.834
recruits a fraction of available p300 and Cbp to BCL6

814
00:47:12.874 --> 00:47:16.743
loci, inducing localized acetylation of chromatin and

815
00:47:16.794 --> 00:47:20.574
BCL6 itself, ultimately driving the transcription of

816
00:47:20.594 --> 00:47:22.774
BCL6-dependent death pathways.

817
00:47:23.874 --> 00:47:27.454
Finally, we assessed the in vivo efficacy of tSIP3, and were

818
